(731, 147, 'site_bookings', '<h4>Site Bookings</h4>\r\nSite bookings are available to purchase online via the website or by phoning the Ag-Grow team on 07 4982 4244. Unless there is a genuine company link, site sharing or piggy backing is not permitted. If in doubt please contact the Administration Office for further information.'),
(732, 147, '_site_bookings', 'field_573c1881f8969'),
(733, 147, 'cancellations', '<h4>Cancellations</h4>\r\nAll cancellations should be received in writing prior to the event. Please confirm the acceptance of this cancellation via the Administration Office.\r\n\r\nOrganizers reserve the right to charge a cancellation fee for costs incurred. For full Terms and Conditions please refer to the back of your booking sheet or website.'),
(734, 147, '_cancellations', 'field_573c189af896a'),
(735, 147, 'site_allocations', '<h4>Site Allocations</h4>\r\n                            <p>The general policy is for exhibitors to be allocated the same site as the year previous. Ag-Grow makes every effort to follow this policy however reserve the right to alter allocations at its own discretion where necessary. Please advise of a special request or specific need when completing your booking by attaching in writing your special booking request.</p>\r\n                            <p>All requests must be in writing or they will not be considered. Initial site allocations are completed by mid June. Please note sites are only allocated on receipt of a completed booking form and deposit. Full payment of sites is required by the 30th of April and must be paid before site allocations will be given.</p>'),
(736, 147, '_site_allocations', 'field_573c18b1f896b'),
(737, 147, 'safety', '<h4>Safety</h4>\r\n                            <p>During Ag-Grow, demonstration vehicles may be moving around the site. Exhibitors should exercise due care particularly when children are present. Fire, Police & Ambulance services are on site over the three days and are based in the David Crouch Pavilion off the Administration Office. General vehicle movement on the QMIX site during the hours of 8.00am  5.00pm is strictly prohibited for safety reasons.</p>'),
(738, 147, '_safety', 'field_573c18bdf896c'),
(739, 147, 'public_liability_insurance', '<h4>Public Liability Insurance</h4>\r\n                            <p>Under new risk management strategies each and every exhibitor must produce a Certificate of Currency of their own public risk insurance. This must show a cover of a minimum $10,000,000. If the Certificate of Currency is not presented to the Administation Office prior to 30 June, Ag-Grow Qmix will obtain Public Liability cover for the site. The cost is $130.00 inc per exhibitor.</p>'),
(740, 147, '_public_liability_insurance', 'field_573c18c9f896d'),
(741, 147, 'health_permits_for_food_exhibitors', '<h4>Health Permits for Food Exhibitors</h4>\r\n                            <p>All food exhibitors must adhere to local council regulations and apply for a temporary catering permit. This is available on request from the Health Department of the Central Highlands Regional Council on 07 4982 8318 or information is available through the Administration Office.</p>\r\n                            <p>This must be arranged prior to the event. The Council have stipulated that all food exhibitors will be policed, to avoid closure please ensure a current permit is obtained.</p>'),
(742, 147, '_health_permits_for_food_exhibitors', 'field_573c18d9f896e'),
(743, 147, 'opening_hours', '<h4>Opening Hours</h4>\r\n                            <p><strong>Ag-Grow QMIX Field Days are open to the General Public from 8:00am to 5:00pm 9th, 10th & 11th July 2013. Packing up prior to 5:00pm on Saturday is strongly discouraged.</strong></p>'),
(744, 147, '_opening_hours', 'field_573c18ecf896f'),
(745, 147, 'administration_office_hours', '<h4>Administration Office Hours</h4>\r\n                            <p>The Administration Office is located in the centre of the field day site.</p>\r\n                            <p>Office hours are 7.00am  6.00pm</p>\r\n                            <p>For after hours assistance, please contact :\r\n                                <br>Donna Reeves\r\n                                <br>Manager: 0423 625 955\r\n                                <br>Geoff Dein\r\n                                <br>Managing Director: 0419 426 013\r\n                            </p>'),
(746, 147, '_administration_office_hours', 'field_573c18f7f8970'),
(747, 147, 'security', '<h4>Security</h4>\r\n                            <p>Professional security service will operate 24 hours on site from Wednesday 5:00pm to 8.00 am Sunday morning. No persons will be allowed on site outside of the field day hours unless prior arrangements have been made.</p>'),
(748, 147, '_security', 'field_573c190bf8971'),
(749, 147, 'exhibitor_passes', ' <h4>Exhibitor Passes</h4>\r\n                            <p>Exhibitor passes are per person basis only. Exhibitor passes are available for collection from the Adminstration Office upon arrival to the site. It is important that passes are collected prior to Thursday to avoid Admission charges.</p>'),
(750, 147, '_exhibitor_passes', 'field_573c1916f8972'),
(751, 147, 'exhibitor_entry_and_parking', '<h4>Exhibitor Entry and Parking</h4>\r\n                            <p>Exhibitor entry to the field day is via the Main Entrance off the Capricorn Highway. Please note that it is not the Exit gate under the main billboard. Free access will only be granted to exhibitor pass holders.</p>\r\n                            <p>Please do not park your vehicle on your site or your neighbours. After unloading your daily supplies exhibitors are requested to park their vehicles in the designated Exhibitor Only parking area. Vehicle movement within the field day perimeter is strictly prohibited between 8.00am & 5:00pm during the three days.</p>'),
(752, 147, '_exhibitor_entry_and_parking', 'field_573c1920f8973');
