(1504, 37, 'ranelle_carter_content', 'Sandi grew up in the Snowy Mountains in southern NSW. Her childhood was spent riding horses through the mountains. Sandi competed in pony club &amp; competed in the junior Man from Snowy River competitions when she was old enough. During her time at boarding school Sandi spent most of her time on horses experimenting with horsemanship. After high school, Sandi headed to Longreach Pastoral College &amp; completed her Diploma of Agriculture &amp; Cert 3 in equine under the watchful eye of John Arnold.'),
