(1759, 293, 'field_demonstrations', '<h4>Field Demonstrations / Seminar</h4>\r\nBoth these activities are very welcome. Should you wish to access an area for these purposes please contact Administration for arrangements and inclusion in the Official Timetable. If product demonstrations are conducted at your site please be considerate of adjoining exhibitors.'),
(1760, 293, '_field_demonstrations', 'field_573c3e143a595'),
(1761, 293, 'permanent_structures', '<h4>Permanent Structures</h4>\r\nPermanent structures are encouraged, however, Council requirements which must be adhered to. The organizers have blanket agreements in place but you must advise Administration Office beforehand to comply with regulations.'),
(1762, 293, '_permanent_structures', 'field_573c3e213a596'),
(1763, 293, 'exhibitors_display', '<h4>Exhibitors Display</h4>\r\nExhibitors are encouraged to present their product in a safe and considerate manner throughout the duration of the field days.'),
(1764, 293, '_exhibitors_display', 'field_573c3e2f3a597'),
(1765, 293, 'excavations', '<h4>Excavations</h4>\r\nUnderground services can seriously damage equipment and facilities if excavating in the wrong area. Please check with the organizers prior to digging to avoid a costly mistake. Main underground power is 415 volts and any contact may result in death by electrocution or require expensive repairs by the Exhibitor.'),
(1766, 293, '_excavations', 'field_573c3e3a3a598'),
(1767, 293, 'power_and_water', '<h4>Power and Water</h4>\r\nPower and water is accessible to all sites within a 30m radius. Every power box has ample 240 volt single phase outlets and three phase power is available on request for heavy industry demonstrations. Please remember to bring your own power leads, power boards, hoses, buckets, rakes etc'),
(1768, 293, '_power_and_water', 'field_573c3e443a599'),
(1769, 293, 'cranes', '<h4>Cranes, Forklifts etc</h4>\r\nCranes, forklifts, a post hole digger and tractor are available free of charge for setting up and dismantling display purposes. These are available on a needs basis and we request your patience. Please note the crane is only available on Tuesday, Wednesday and Sunday.\r\n\r\nOutside these days you are encouraged to make your own arrangement with Walter Wright Cranes Australia on 07 4987 4908. A heavy duty loading ramp is located adjacent to the wash bay area with high pressure cleaners to help keep equipment presentable.'),
(1770, 293, '_cranes', 'field_573c3e503a59a'),
(1771, 293, 'site_improvements', '<h4>Site Improvements</h4>\r\nHay bales, sawdust and bark chips are available to enhance your display. Booking is essential and orders will be delivered on Wednesday. Improvements will not be delivered until you notify Administration of your arrival and these improvements will be promptly delivered. It is the responsibility of the Exhibitor to utilize their site improvements to their own specifications.'),
(1772, 293, '_site_improvements', 'field_573c3e613a59b'),
(1773, 293, 'livestock_and_panels', '<h4>Livestock and Panels</h4>\r\nLivestock exhibitors have access to loading ramps (fixed or portable) and wash bay facilities. Panels are available for each site and must be ordered prior to the event. Panels are also available for sale. Contact Administration Office for details. Panels will be delivered to each site as ordered prior to the event and exhibitors are requested to dismantle and pile their panels on departure.'),
(1774, 293, '_livestock_and_panels', 'field_573c3e6b3a59c'),
(1775, 293, 'nlis', '<h4>NLIS &amp; Tick Spraying for Cattle Exhibitors at Ag-Grow</h4>\r\nTo assist you we have made arrangements for all exhibited cattle over the age of 2 years to be read and registered, this will be conducted on the Thursday morning at your site. It would be appreciated if your PIC number is available for reading if necessary.\r\n\r\nAg-Grow Management will also negotiate with the DPI for exhibitors, who are required to cross a tick line, to have their cattle sprayed at the Ag-Grow grounds. If this applies, exhibitors are requested to contact Ag-Grow to provide approximate numbers.'),
(1776, 293, '_nlis', 'field_573c3e793a59d'),
