(2004, 332, 'managing_director_subheading', 'This year we reflect on the 25 year history of Westpac Aggrow, one of the States most successful field day events.\r\n<img class="size-medium wp-image-331 aligncenter" src="http://aggrow.stagingdevsite.com/dev/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/adam-white-1-300x221.jpg" alt="adam-white" width="300" height="221" />'),
(2005, 332, '_managing_director_subheading', 'field_573c085d481a3'),
(2006, 333, 'managing_director_subheading', 'This year we reflect on the 25 year history of Westpac Aggrow, one of the States most successful field day events.'),
(2007, 333, '_managing_director_subheading', 'field_573c085d481a3'),
(2010, 337, 'site_bookings', '<h4>Site Bookings</h4>\r\nSite bookings are available to purchase online via the website or by phoning the Ag-Grow team on 07 4982 4244. Unless there is a genuine company link, site sharing or piggy backing is not permitted. If in doubt please contact the Administration Office for further information.'),
(2011, 337, '_site_bookings', 'field_573c1881f8969'),
(2012, 337, 'cancellations', '<h4>Cancellations</h4>\r\nAll cancellations should be received in writing prior to the event. Please confirm the acceptance of this cancellation via the Administration Office.\r\n\r\nOrganizers reserve the right to charge a cancellation fee for costs incurred. For full Terms and Conditions please refer to the back of your booking sheet or website.'),
(2013, 337, '_cancellations', 'field_573c189af896a'),
(2014, 337, 'site_allocations', '<h4>Site Allocations</h4>\r\nThe general policy is for exhibitors to be allocated the same site as the year previous. Ag-Grow makes every effort to follow this policy however reserve the right to alter allocations at its own discretion where necessary. Please advise of a special request or specific need when completing your booking by attaching in writing your special booking request.\r\n\r\nAll requests must be in writing or they will not be considered. Initial site allocations are completed by mid June. Please note sites are only allocated on receipt of a completed booking form and deposit. Full payment of sites is required by the 30th of April and must be paid before site allocations will be given.'),
(2015, 337, '_site_allocations', 'field_573c18b1f896b'),
(2016, 337, 'safety', '<h4>Safety</h4>\r\nDuring Ag-Grow, demonstration vehicles may be moving around the site. Exhibitors should exercise due care particularly when children are present. Fire, Police &amp; Ambulance services are on site over the three days and are based in the David Crouch Pavilion off the Administration Office. General vehicle movement on the QMIX site during the hours of 8.00am  5.00pm is strictly prohibited for safety reasons.'),
(2017, 337, '_safety', 'field_573c18bdf896c'),
(2018, 337, 'public_liability_insurance', '<h4>Public Liability Insurance</h4>\r\nUnder new risk management strategies each and every exhibitor must produce a Certificate of Currency of their own public risk insurance. This must show a cover of a minimum $10,000,000. If the Certificate of Currency is not presented to the Administation Office prior to 30 June, Ag-Grow Qmix will obtain Public Liability cover for the site. The cost is $130.00 inc per exhibitor.'),
(2019, 337, '_public_liability_insurance', 'field_573c18c9f896d'),
(2020, 337, 'health_permits_for_food_exhibitors', '<h4>Health Permits for Food Exhibitors</h4>\r\nAll food exhibitors must adhere to local council regulations and apply for a temporary catering permit. This is available on request from the Health Department of the Central Highlands Regional Council on 07 4982 8318 or information is available through the Administration Office.\r\n\r\nThis must be arranged prior to the event. The Council have stipulated that all food exhibitors will be policed, to avoid closure please ensure a current permit is obtained.'),
(2021, 337, '_health_permits_for_food_exhibitors', 'field_573c18d9f896e'),
(2022, 337, 'opening_hours', '<h4>Opening Hours</h4>\r\n<strong>Ag-Grow QMIX Field Days are open to the General Public from 8:00am to 5:00pm 9th, 10th &amp; 11th July 2013. Packing up prior to 5:00pm on Saturday is strongly discouraged.</strong>'),
(2023, 337, '_opening_hours', 'field_573c18ecf896f'),
(2024, 337, 'administration_office_hours', '<h4>Administration Office Hours</h4>\r\nThe Administration Office is located in the centre of the field day site.\r\nOffice hours are 7.00am  6.00pm\r\nFor after hours assistance, please contact :\r\nDonna Reeves\r\nManager: 0423 625 955\r\nGeoff Dein\r\nManaging Director: 0419 426 013'),
(2025, 337, '_administration_office_hours', 'field_573c18f7f8970'),
(2026, 337, 'security', '<h4>Security</h4>\r\nProfessional security service will operate 24 hours on site from Wednesday 5:00pm to 8.00 am Sunday morning. No persons will be allowed on site outside of the field day hours unless prior arrangements have been made.'),
(2027, 337, '_security', 'field_573c190bf8971'),
(2028, 337, 'exhibitor_passes', '<h4>Exhibitor Passes</h4>\r\nExhibitor passes are per person basis only. Exhibitor passes are available for collection from the Adminstration Office upon arrival to the site. It is important that passes are collected prior to Thursday to avoid Admission charges.'),
(2029, 337, '_exhibitor_passes', 'field_573c1916f8972'),
(2030, 337, 'exhibitor_entry_and_parking', '<h4>Exhibitor Entry and Parking</h4>\r\nExhibitor entry to the field day is via the Main Entrance off the Capricorn Highway. Please note that it is not the Exit gate under the main billboard. Free access will only be granted to exhibitor pass holders.\r\n\r\nPlease do not park your vehicle on your site or your neighbours. After unloading your daily supplies exhibitors are requested to park their vehicles in the designated Exhibitor Only parking area. Vehicle movement within the field day perimeter is strictly prohibited between 8.00am &amp; 5:00pm during the three days.'),
(2031, 337, '_exhibitor_entry_and_parking', 'field_573c1920f8973'),
(2032, 337, 'eftpos_facilities', '<h4>EFTPOS Facilities</h4>\r\nEftpos facilities are located at the Administration Office.'),
(2033, 337, '_eftpos_facilities', 'field_573c192bf8974'),
(2034, 337, 'money_change', '<h4>Money / Change</h4>\r\nExhibitors must make own arrangements with local banks in relation cash floats for their site.'),
(2035, 337, '_money_change', 'field_573c1939f8975'),
(2036, 337, 'freight_contacts', '<h4>Freight Contacts</h4>\r\nEmerald Carrying Company  Emerald Depot 07 4982 3488\r\nNQX  Emerald Depot 07 4982 2310\r\nFollowmont  07 4982 4593'),
(2037, 337, '_freight_contacts', 'field_573c1971f8976'),
(2038, 337, 'hire_companies', '<h4>Hire Companies</h4>\r\nUnderwoods  07 4035 4513\r\nParty Events  07 4922 4402\r\nNJ Canvas Party Hire  07 4630 1400\r\nSmith &amp; Co Tent Hire  07 4982 1850\r\nInstant Marquee Hire  07 4922 8833\r\nFlexihire  07 4982 3488\r\nCoates Hire  07 4982 4186'),
(2039, 337, '_hire_companies', 'field_573c1979f8977'),
(2040, 337, 'never_ending', '<h4>Never-ending options at Ag-Grow Field Days</h4>\r\nCompanies often approach Administration staff with a desire to attend or have a presence at the field days but do not wish to take the tradition option of a static display. Currently there is a number of sponsorships or internal advertising within the field days, that may assist your company in gaining more direct access to your target demographic.\r\n\r\nAll packages are individually tailored to produce the best results within your budget for your company. Contact Administration and allow us to assist you to shine the spotlight on your company.'),
(2041, 337, '_never_ending', 'field_573c1988f8978'),
(2042, 337, 'launching', '<h4>Launching a new product or service</h4>\r\nWe will gladly assist you in promoting your company and/or product. Please contact the Administration Office for further assistance.'),
(2043, 337, '_launching', 'field_573c1996f8979'),
(2044, 337, 'ag-grow_website', '<h4>Ag-Grow Website</h4>\r\nUpon booking a site, your company will automatically be advertised via the Current Event Information page when activated in June on the Ag-Grow website (www.aggrow.com.au). To achieve the best coverage, please ensure that the Administration Office receives your current web address, contact details and product listing.'),
(2045, 337, '_ag-grow_website', 'field_573c19a3f897a'),
(2046, 337, 'ag-grows_official_handbook', '<h4>Ag-Grows Official Handbook</h4>\r\nThe Aggrow QMIX handbook is compiled by our corporate partners, the Queensland Country Life and is inserted into approximately 25,000 newspapers throughout Queensland. It is also available to all exhibitors and visitors to Ag-Grow and QMIX. It will be used as a point of future reference for enquiring clients.\r\n\r\nIf you are serious about gaining market share at Ag-Grow, advertising in the Handbook is a must. Booking and copy deadline is 1st June 2015. Pleases contact John Thompson on 07 4927 9422.'),
(2047, 337, '_ag-grows_official_handbook', 'field_573c19aef897b'),
(2048, 337, 'radio', '<h4>Radio, TV and Press</h4>\r\nAg-Grow uses an extensive combination of the media to ensure that the Central Highlands and surrounding regions are aware of this annual meeting and marketing event. An intensive and thorough promotional campaign is conducted from May through to July. Should you wish to participate in this campaign to promote your company and its involvement, please contact the Administration Office who will assist you in contacting the right people for your chosen advertising media.'),
(2049, 337, '_radio', 'field_573c19b9f897c'),
(2050, 337, 'company_flags', '<h4>Company Flags</h4>\r\nAg-Grow have erected a number of flag poles around the site for companys to use. Flags can be placed on your site and on the promenade during the three days. Please inform the Ag-Grow Administration Office if your company would like to take advantage of this opportunity.'),
(2051, 337, '_company_flags', 'field_573c19c8f897d'),
(2052, 337, 'product_listing_forms', '<h4>Product Listing Forms</h4>\r\nTo correctly promote your site and business we require a current Product Listing Form to be completed. Please contact the Administration Office if you require a new form.'),
(2053, 337, '_product_listing_forms', 'field_573c19d5f897e'),
(2054, 337, 'pa_announcements', '<h4>PA Announcements</h4>\r\nA public address system operates during the three days as part of your package. Ag-Grow has a professional Announcer to advertise your product or services. It is the exhibitors responsibility to ensure the Administration Office has received your companys PA announcement. During the event interviews should be conducted with the Announcer to raise your companys profile. To arrange an interview please enquire at the field days Administration Office.'),
(2055, 337, '_pa_announcements', 'field_573c19e4f897f'),
(2056, 337, 'radio_announcements', '<h4>Radio Announcements</h4>\r\nEmerald 4HI are located in the Ag Pavilion and broadcast live from their site on Tuesday, Wednesday and Thursday of the field days.'),
(2057, 337, '_radio_announcements', 'field_573c19f0f8980'),
(2058, 161, 'rule', 'a:5:{s:5:"param";s:4:"page";s:8:"operator";s:2:"==";s:5:"value";s:2:"23";s:8:"order_no";i:0;s:8:"group_no";i:0;}'),
(2059, 338, 'setting-up_display', '<h4>Setting-up Display</h4>\r\nExhibitors are encouraged to complete setting up the display as early as possible to avoid congestion on Opening Day. A caretaker is on site and exhibitors may gain access to their site after 1st July.\r\n\r\nExhibitors are reminded to confirm the site with Administration prior to setting up and are requested to strictly adhere to the boundaries of their display area. All displays must be completely set up by 8:00am Thursday 9th July 2015.'),
(2060, 338, '_setting-up_display', 'field_573c3e073a594'),
(2061, 338, 'demonstrations', '<h4>Field Demonstrations / Seminar</h4>\r\nBoth these activities are very welcome. Should you wish to access an area for these purposes please contact Administration for arrangements and inclusion in the Official Timetable. If product demonstrations are conducted at your site please be considerate of adjoining exhibitors.'),
(2062, 338, '_demonstrations', 'field_573c3e143a595'),
(2063, 338, 'permanent_structures', '<h4>Permanent Structures</h4>\r\nPermanent structures are encouraged, however, Council requirements which must be adhered to. The organizers have blanket agreements in place but you must advise Administration Office beforehand to comply with regulations.'),
(2064, 338, '_permanent_structures', 'field_573c3e213a596'),
(2065, 338, 'exhibitors_display', '<h4>Exhibitors Display</h4>\r\nExhibitors are encouraged to present their product in a safe and considerate manner throughout the duration of the field days.'),
(2066, 338, '_exhibitors_display', 'field_573c3e2f3a597'),
(2067, 338, 'excavations', '<h4>Excavations</h4>\r\nUnderground services can seriously damage equipment and facilities if excavating in the wrong area. Please check with the organizers prior to digging to avoid a costly mistake. Main underground power is 415 volts and any contact may result in death by electrocution or require expensive repairs by the Exhibitor.'),
(2068, 338, '_excavations', 'field_573c3e3a3a598'),
(2069, 338, 'power_and_water', '<h4>Power and Water</h4>\r\nPower and water is accessible to all sites within a 30m radius. Every power box has ample 240 volt single phase outlets and three phase power is available on request for heavy industry demonstrations. Please remember to bring your own power leads, power boards, hoses, buckets, rakes etc'),
(2070, 338, '_power_and_water', 'field_573c3e443a599'),
(2071, 338, 'cranes', '<h4>Cranes, Forklifts etc</h4>\r\nCranes, forklifts, a post hole digger and tractor are available free of charge for setting up and dismantling display purposes. These are available on a needs basis and we request your patience. Please note the crane is only available on Tuesday, Wednesday and Sunday.\r\n\r\nOutside these days you are encouraged to make your own arrangement with Walter Wright Cranes Australia on 07 4987 4908. A heavy duty loading ramp is located adjacent to the wash bay area with high pressure cleaners to help keep equipment presentable.'),
(2072, 338, '_cranes', 'field_573c3e503a59a'),
(2073, 338, 'site_improvements', '<h4>Site Improvements</h4>\r\nHay bales, sawdust and bark chips are available to enhance your display. Booking is essential and orders will be delivered on Wednesday. Improvements will not be delivered until you notify Administration of your arrival and these improvements will be promptly delivered. It is the responsibility of the Exhibitor to utilize their site improvements to their own specifications.'),
(2074, 338, '_site_improvements', 'field_573c3e613a59b'),
(2075, 338, 'livestock_and_panels', '<h4>Livestock and Panels</h4>\r\nLivestock exhibitors have access to loading ramps (fixed or portable) and wash bay facilities. Panels are available for each site and must be ordered prior to the event. Panels are also available for sale. Contact Administration Office for details. Panels will be delivered to each site as ordered prior to the event and exhibitors are requested to dismantle and pile their panels on departure.'),
(2076, 338, '_livestock_and_panels', 'field_573c3e6b3a59c'),
(2077, 338, 'nlis', '<h4>NLIS &amp; Tick Spraying for Cattle Exhibitors at Ag-Grow</h4>\r\nTo assist you we have made arrangements for all exhibited cattle over the age of 2 years to be read and registered, this will be conducted on the Thursday morning at your site. It would be appreciated if your PIC number is available for reading if necessary.\r\n\r\nAg-Grow Management will also negotiate with the DPI for exhibitors, who are required to cross a tick line, to have their cattle sprayed at the Ag-Grow grounds. If this applies, exhibitors are requested to contact Ag-Grow to provide approximate numbers.'),
(2078, 338, '_nlis', 'field_573c3e793a59d'),
(2079, 23, 'demonstrations', '<h4>Field Demonstrations / Seminar</h4>\r\nBoth these activities are very welcome. Should you wish to access an area for these purposes please contact Administration for arrangements and inclusion in the Official Timetable. If product demonstrations are conducted at your site please be considerate of adjoining exhibitors.'),
(2080, 23, '_demonstrations', 'field_573c3e143a595'),
(2083, 342, 'working_cattle_title', 'Catch the live action of skilled cattle dogs.'),
(2084, 342, '_working_cattle_title', 'field_573d9a57dfcd0'),
(2085, 342, 'working_cattle_content', '<strong>Dont miss out on the Ag-Grow experience</strong>\r\n\r\nA dog is truly a mans best friend when handling cattle with this precision. The dog trials have been with us for over 20 years and have not wavered once during that time.\r\n\r\nAs the dogs and their masters compete with one another to handle a herd of cattle around an obstacle course they are allotted points in the overall competition.\r\n\r\nThe winner is announced before the ever popular Cattle Dog Auction on day 3 of the event. Competitors come from far and wide to compete in this event which remains as poplar today as it was 20 years ago.'),
(2086, 342, '_working_cattle_content', 'field_573d9a9ddfcd1'),
