(3888, 600, 'luke_bennett_content', 'Ron grew up in Springsure, where he was involved in Pony club. He then completed a two year course at the Emerald Agricultural College. From college he headed north. First Ron worked at Mt Hope with Allan Wallace, then to Moray with Robert Durkin and Laurie Heading, where he got involved in Campdrafting. After that he went to Millungera with Evan Acton, where Ron got more involved in Campdrafting and Stockman Challenges. While at Millungera he got to do clinics with Pat Parelli, Ray Hunt and Graham Ward also Ken May came to Millungera on many occasions for week long clinics.'),
